[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m First, let me recall that in any base b, the number 17_b represents 1*b^1 + 7*b^0, which is b + 7. Similarly, 97_b is 9*b + 7. So the problem is asking for bases b > 9 such that b + 7 divides 9b + 7. In other words, (b + 7) divides (9b + 7). 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m So, mathematically, I need to find all integers b > 9 where (b + 7) divides (9b + 7). Let me write that as:
