[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### Step 1: Express the numbers in base $ b $
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m In base $ b $, the numbers $ 17_b $ and $ 97_b $ can be written as:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 17_b = 1 \cdot b + 7 = b + 7
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 97_b = 9 \cdot b + 7 = 9b + 7
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m We want $ 17_b $ to divide $ 97_b $, i.e.,
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m (b + 7) \mid (9b + 7)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m This means that $ (b + 7) $ must be a **divisor of $ 9b + 7 $**.
