[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### Step 1: Define Variables and Equations
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Let:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - $ s $ be the speed in km/h
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - $ t $ be the time in minutes spent in the coffee shop
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - $ T $ be the total time (in minutes) taken for the walk including the coffee shop
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m We are told:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - When walking at $ s $ km/h, the total time is 4 hours (i.e., 240 minutes), including $ t $ minutes in the coffee shop.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - So:  
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   \frac{9}{s} \text{ hours} + t \text{ minutes} = 240 \text{ minutes}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   Convert $ \frac{9}{s} $ hours to minutes:  
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   \frac{9}{s} \times 60 = 240 - t
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - When walking at $ s + 2 $ km/h, the total time is 2 hours and 24 minutes (i.e., 144 minutes), including $ t $ minutes in the coffee shop:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   \frac{9}{s + 2} \text{ hours} + t \text{ minutes} = 144 \text{ minutes}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   Convert $ \frac{9}{s + 2} $ hours to minutes:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   \frac{9}{s + 2} \times 60 = 144 - t
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m   $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### Step 2: Set Up the Equations
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m We now have the two equations:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 1. $ \frac{540}{s} = 240 - t $  
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 2. $ \frac{540}{s + 2} = 144 - t $
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### Step 3: Solve the System of Equations
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Let’s solve the system by expressing $ t $ from both equations and equating them:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m From (1):
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m t = 240 - \frac{540}{s}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m From (2):
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m t = 144 - \frac{540}{s + 2}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Equating:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 240 - \frac{540}{s} = 144 - \frac{540}{s + 2}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Simplify:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 96 = \frac{540}{s} - \frac{540}{s + 2}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Factor 540:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 96 = 540 \left( \frac{1}{s} - \frac{1}{s + 2} \right)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Simplify the difference of fractions:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \frac{1}{s} - \frac{1}{s + 2} = \frac{(s + 2) - s}{s(s + 2)} = \frac{2}{s(s + 2)}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m So:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 96 = 540 \cdot \frac{2}{s(s + 2)}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 96 = \frac{1080}{s(s + 2)}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Multiply both sides by $ s(s + 2) $:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 96s(s + 2) = 1080
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Divide both sides by 24:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 4s(s + 2) = 45
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m s^2 + 2s - \frac{45}{4} = 0
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Solve this quadratic equation:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m s = \frac{-2 \pm \sqrt{4 + 45}}{2} = \frac{-2 \pm \sqrt{49}}{2} = \frac{-2 \pm 7}{2}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m s = \frac{5}{2} = 2.5 \text{ km/h}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### Step 4: Find $ t $
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Plug $ s = 2.5 $ into the first equation:
