[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### Step 1: Set Up Equations
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m From the given data, the time spent walking (in hours) is:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - For speed $ s $: $ \frac{9}{s} = 4 - \frac{t}{60} $
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - For speed $ s + 2 $: $ \frac{9}{s + 2} = 2.4 - \frac{t}{60} $
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Let’s define $ x = \frac{t}{60} $, so that the equations become:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 1. $ \frac{9}{s} = 4 - x $
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 2. $ \frac{9}{s + 2} = 2.4 - x $
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### Step 2: Solve for $ s $ and $ x $
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m From the first equation:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m s = \frac{9}{4 - x}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Substitute into the second equation:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \frac{9}{\frac{9}{4 - x} + 2} = 2.4 - x
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Simplify the denominator:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \frac{9}{\frac{9 + 2(4 - x)}{4 - x}} = 2.4 - x \Rightarrow \frac{9(4 - x)}{17 - 2x} = 2.4 - x
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Multiply both sides by $ 17 - 2x $:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 9(4 - x) = (2.4 - x)(17 - 2x)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
