[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - **At speed $ s + 2 $ km/h**, the total time is **2 hours and 24 minutes**.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m We are to find the total time (in minutes) when Aya walks at speed $ s + \frac{1}{2} $ km/h, **including the t minutes spent in the coffee shop**.
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### **Step 2: Convert all times to consistent units**
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - Total time at $ s $ km/h: 4 hours = 4 hours
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m - Total time at $ s + 2 $ km/h: 2 hours 24 minutes = 2.4 hours
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Since $ t $ is in minutes, we convert it to hours:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m t = \frac{t}{60} \text{ hours}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### **Step 3: Set up equations based on distance, speed, and time**
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Let the time Aya walks be $ t_w $ (in hours). Then:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \text{Time walking} = \frac{9}{s} \text{ hours}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m So the total time (including coffee shop) is:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \frac{9}{s} + \frac{t}{60} = 4 \quad \text{(Equation 1)}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \frac{9}{s + 2} + \frac{t}{60} = 2.4 \quad \text{(Equation 2)}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### **Step 4: Solve the system of equations**
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m From Equation (1):
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \frac{9}{s} = 4 - \frac{t}{60}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \Rightarrow t = 60 \left(4 - \frac{9}{s}\right) = 240 - \frac{540}{s} \quad \text{(Equation 1a)}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m From Equation (2):
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \frac{9}{s + 2} = 2.4 - \frac{t}{60}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \Rightarrow t = 60 \left(2.4 - \frac{9}{s + 2}\right) = 144 - \frac{540}{s + 2} \quad \text{(Equation 2a)}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Now set Equation (1a) equal to Equation (2a):
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 240 - \frac{540}{s} = 144 - \frac{540}{s + 2}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \Rightarrow 96 = \frac{540}{s} - \frac{540}{s + 2}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Factor 540:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 96 = 540 \left( \frac{1}{s} - \frac{1}{s + 2} \right)
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \Rightarrow 96 = 540 \cdot \frac{2}{s(s + 2)}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \Rightarrow 96 = \frac{1080}{s(s + 2)}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Multiply both sides by $ s(s + 2) $:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 96s(s + 2) = 1080
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \Rightarrow s(s + 2) = \frac{1080}{96} = 11.25
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \Rightarrow s^2 + 2s - 11.25 = 0
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Solve the quadratic:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m s = \frac{-2 \pm \sqrt{4 + 45}}{2} = \frac{-2 \pm \sqrt{49}}{2} = \frac{-2 \pm 7}{2}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \Rightarrow s = \frac{5}{2} = 2.5 \text{ km/h}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### **Step 5: Find $ t $**
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Use Equation (1a):
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m t = 240 - \frac{540}{2.5} = 240 - 216 = 24 \text{ minutes}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ### **Step 6: Find the total time at $ s + \frac{1}{2} $**
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Now, find the time at speed $ s + \frac{1}{2} = 2.5 + 0.5 = 3 $ km/h:
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m \text{Time walking} = \frac{9}{3} = 3 \text{ hours}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m Add the t minutes (24 minutes):
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 3 \text{ hours} = 180 \text{ minutes}, \quad \text{Total time} = 180 + 24 = 204 \text{ minutes}
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m $$
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m ---
[36m(TaskRunner pid=202387)[0m 
